    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "ok that makes sense. so it's basically just a neutral person or company holding the money so nobody gets cheated? like, who actually manages the money while it's in there and how do they make sure it stays safe?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "That's a great way to think about it - a neutral third-party holding the funds. In Toronto, the escrow account is typically managed by a title company or a law firm that specializes in real estate transactions. They're responsible for holding the funds and ensuring that they're disbursed according to the terms of the sale. The escrow company is usually a separate entity from the title company, and they work together to manage the escrow account and facilitate the transfer of funds.\n\nAs for safety, escrow companies are regulated by the government and are required to follow strict guidelines to protect the funds. They're also insured, which provides an additional layer of protection for the funds. It's a bit like having a group of watchful eyes on the money, making sure it's not being misappropriated or mishandled. The escrow company will also keep records of all transactions, including deposits and withdrawals, so that everything is transparent and auditable.",
